# What is Cloud Computing?
Delivery of on-demand computing resources over the internet on a pay-per-use basis
# Cloud Models
## Private Cloud
- Used exclusively by a business/organization.
- Services are delivered over a private network.
- Hosted by on-prem datacenters or dedicated hardware hosted by a third party provider â€” involves ==CAPEX==.
- More control, higher flexibility, higher maintenance.
## Public Cloud
- Has a shared environment operated by a third-party provider
- Computing resources are delivered on-demand, typically over the internet
- Lower cost, less maintenance
## Hybrid Cloud
- Combination of public and private cloud
- Use existing investments in your datacenters
- Higher control on resources and data
- Higher flexibility to choose where to deploy resources

# Azure availability 
Azure services are available in countries with multiple regions for Disaster recoveries Or Fault tolerance.
## Regions
One country can have multiple [[Great Learning/GL-Regions|Regions]].

```mermaid 
graph TD
    A[Country] --> B[Region_1]
    A --> C[Region_2]
    A -->D[Region_3]
```

## Types/Flavors
Available as:
- **Public cloud**
- **Azure Government**
	- Governments tenants have complete Isolated environment to outside world.
	- Service improvements and new feature updates will be slow.
- **Deploy on-prem**
	- Microsoft provides few cloud services that can be deployed in On-premises -- ==Identify cloud services that can be deployed in On-premises==

## Marketplace
Marketplace is a store where you can see third-party services that are made available in Azure for use.
These services SLA is not provided by Microsoft.
